{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
The ordering of the commits.  And the greying out of merges from master back to the issue branch.  The ease of navigation back to all the Pull Requests, and the description of the pull request (although links to the jira issue would be sweet.)
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
The commit dates are LIES!  It's telling me that a Commit Date is yesterday, when I know it's about 30 seconds ago.  
If timezones aren't implemented properly yet can we see the actual times instead of relative ones?
{panel}

{panel:title=Available in the Stash Auto-Unapprove Plugin}
This functionality was added to the Atlassian Labs [Auto-Unapprove plugin|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.atlassian.stash.plugin.stash-auto-unapprove-plugin] on marketplace and is not included in Stash's core offering. Please install that plugin if you'd like to automatically remove the approval of any reviewers on a push to the source branch.
{panel}



It looks like if someone commits to a pull request that I've already "Approved", the approval doesn't seem to be removed. Can this be changed, or configured in some way?

Line 163 in {{service.bat}} reads:
{noformat}
call "%~dp0\bin\permgenservice.bat".
{noformat}
It should be:
{noformat}
call "%~dp0permgenservice.bat".
{noformat}
As a result, {{permgenservice.bat}} never runs and Stash fails to startup as a service.

*Rating*: :) Good

