Anyway, the main point of my feedback was to ask if you can remove yourself from a pull request. I'm one of 5 on a particular pull request. And it is very active so I get a lot of e-mails about it and I really don't care. I don't even intend to review it since enough other people have.
{panel}

As pointed out by a customer in a support case, if the Stash server has not been entered in the pg_hba.conf file, Postgres 9 will not allow the connection. The pg_hba.conf file enables client authentication between the PostgreSQL server and the client application. This file consists of a series of entries , which define a host and its associated permissions (e.g., the database it is allowed to connect to, the authentication method to use, and so on). Without this configuration, a similar exception is reported when connecting to Postgres 9:
{noformat}
org.apache.commons.dbcp.SQLNestedException: Cannot create PoolableConnectionFactory (FATAL: password authentication failed for user "<username>")
{noformat}
Please update the [Connecting Stash to Postgres|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/STASH/Connecting+Stash+to+PostgreSQL] document to add the requirement to include Stash server in the above file.
More details about this file are [here|http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.2/static/auth-pg-hba-conf.html].
